HEADWORD: Sixty
<hw>Six"ty</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>siextig</ets>; akin to G. <ets>sechzig</ets>, Goth.
<ets>sa⟦iacute⟧hs tigjus</ets>. See <er>Six</er>, <er>Ten</er>, and cf.
<er>Sixteen</er>.]</ety> <def>Six times ten; fifty-nine and one more;
threescore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sixty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sixty
<hw>Six"ty</hw>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Sixties</plw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The sum of six times ten; sixty
units or objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A symbol representing sixty units, as 60, lx., or
LX.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sixty-fourth</ent>⟦br⟧
